Click on the Pages icon  on the far left icon   

Click on +Page 

Click on Other ways to add a page 

Enter a page name 

Uncheck the Add page to main navigation if you do not want it to appear in the site menu navigation bar 

Select Start from blank 

Click Add 

Add a Text component to the page section 

Use Heading 2 as the text type 

Add the page heading 

Click on the + icon directly below the heading text when it is selected (Add a component) and add a standard text field 

Use paragraph as the text type and add any description about the page. 

Under Edit background change the colour of the header section 

Click on the Add section link to add a new section for forms, information etc. 

To create  a new page you can also duplicated an existing one. There is a template page in the Other pages section. 

The tab may appear when previewed using the details of the copied page. From Power Pages Management select the Web Pages option, then the new form. 

Under the General tab select the localized content form and scroll down to Content to update the title. 
